CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779034269
OL,3,CRace hate crimes 'spiralling out of
OL,4,Ccontrol'
OL,6,FIt is the highest number since records
OL,7,Fbegan in 2004.
OL,9,FPolice said they received reports that
OL,10,Fthe family in Strathfoyle had been
OL,11,Freceiving verbal abuse "over a number
OL,12,Fof weeks" and reports "mud and water
OL,13,Fballoons had been thrown at the
OL,14,Fproperty".
OL,16,FThe police said: "A number of young
OL,17,Fpeople have been spoken to by police
OL,18,Fin relation to this matter, which is
OL,19,Fbeing treated as a racially motivated
OL,20,Fhate crime.
OL,26,@sD@XOUtD@IO]tD@WOUvD@IO]xD@ROU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/6
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779034269
OL,3,CRace hate crimes 'spiralling out of
OL,4,Ccontrol'
OL,6,F"Officers from the Neighbourhood
OL,7,FPolicing Team will continue to engage
OL,8,Fwith the community, however racially
OL,9,Fmotivated crime is unacceptable in
OL,10,Ftoday's society and police will deal
OL,11,Fwith any reports robustly."
OL,13,FPatrick Corrigan, Amnesty
OL,14,FInternational's Northern Ireland
OL,15,Fdirector, raised concern about racist
OL,16,Fviolence in Northern Ireland which he
OL,17,Fsaid is "spiralling out of control".
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@[O]yD@IOUyD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/6
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1779034269
OL,3,CRace hate crimes 'spiralling out of
OL,4,Ccontrol'
OL,6,F"For years, minoritised communities
OL,7,Fhave warned that racism is becoming
OL,8,Fnormalised, and these record figures
OL,9,Fshow those warnings were not heeded,"
OL,10,Fhe said.
OL,12,F"The Stormont Executive has failed to
OL,13,Fprotect Northern Ireland's
OL,14,Fincreasingly diverse society and has
OL,15,Fleft many people feeling unsafe in
OL,16,Ftheir own communities.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@eO]tD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/6
